    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-03T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="958"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d958">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.404/453: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-04T00:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 4 [<hi rend="italic">6</hi>], 1941—midnight [<hi rend="italic"
                                >noon</hi>]</date>.<lb/>[Received October 6—2:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1765. Department’s 1112, October 2, 7 p.m., and Embassy’s 1758, October 4, noon.
                    At a conference with representatives of the foreign press on October 4, reported
                    in the Moscow papers, October 5, Lozovski,<note n="34" xml:id="d958fn34">Solomon
                        Abramovich Lozovsky.</note> the Assistant Commissar for Foreign Affairs,
                    read a lengthy prepared statement regarding freedom of worship in the Soviet
                    Union. This statement was unquestionably that promised by Oumansky and mentioned
                    in my telegram under reference. The full text of Lozovski’s prepared statement
                    and of his responses to questions propounded by the newspaper correspondents
                    follows in a telegram bearing the next successive number.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
